divs: Sighting DetailsSighting Report: As I was driving up Route 44 in Winsted, CT, I was driving past the Winsted Animal Hospital at approximately 6:00 p.m. I saw at a 45 degree angle, if one were looking at a clock the object was at 1:00 in the sky. It was a pink, circular shape that appeared to look like it had a pink diamond that was sparkling in the middle. It lasted for approximately 10 seconds and it went from appearing rather large to vanishing.
